# Deploy Rules — Render Infrastructure

## Blueprint Is the Single Source of Truth

All Render infrastructure MUST be defined in `render.yaml` at the repository root.

**Mandatory:**
- Every service, database, env var group, and configuration lives in `render.yaml`
- Changes to infrastructure go through a PR that modifies `render.yaml`
- No manual service creation via the Render Dashboard or MCP direct-creation tools

**Forbidden:**
- Creating services via `create_web_service`, `create_static_site`, or any MCP creation tool
- Manually adding env vars through the Dashboard (use `sync: false` in the blueprint)
- Changing plans, regions, or scaling outside the blueprint

## Architecture

| Service                          | Type   | Name       | Runtime |
| -------------------------------- | ------ | ---------- | ------- |
| Marketing site (arvid.work)      | static | arvid-site | static  |
| Dashboard + login (app.arvid.work) | static | arvid-web  | static  |
| Express API (BFF)                | web    | arvid-api  | node    |

## Domain Mapping

- `arvid.work` — Cloudflare CNAME → `arvid-site.onrender.com`
- `app.arvid.work` — Cloudflare CNAME → `arvid-web.onrender.com`
- `arvid-api.onrender.com` — default Render URL (no custom domain)

Custom domains added in Render Dashboard under Settings > Custom Domains after first deploy.

## Environment Variables

### arvid-site (set in Dashboard after deploy)
- `VITE_APP_URL` — full URL to the dashboard app, e.g. `https://app.arvid.work`

### arvid-web (set in Dashboard after deploy)
- `VITE_API_BASE` — full URL to the API server including path prefix, e.g. `https://arvid-api.onrender.com/api`
- `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` — Supabase project URL
- `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` — Supabase publishable/anon key

### arvid-api (set in Dashboard after deploy)
- `SUPABASE_URL` — Supabase project URL
- `SUPABASE_KEY` — Supabase service key
- `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` — OpenRouter API key for AI summaries
- `SITE_ORIGIN` — `https://arvid.work` (CORS)
- `APP_ORIGIN` — `https://app.arvid.work` (CORS)
- `NODE_ENV` — hardcoded to `production` in blueprint
- `PORT` — auto-injected by Render

## Two Vite Builds

- `vite.config.ts` — builds dashboard app from `src/app/`, outputs to `dist/`
- `vite.config.site.ts` — builds marketing site from `src/site/`, outputs to `dist-site/`

## Code Constraints for Deployability

- Server must bind to `0.0.0.0:$PORT` (Express default + explicit in `server/index.ts`)
- No hardcoded credentials — all secrets via `process.env`
- Frontend API base must read from `import.meta.env.VITE_API_BASE` with `/api` fallback for local dev
- Shared schemas in `shared/` are consumed by both frontend and server — changes trigger both builds
- Marketing site links use `import.meta.env.VITE_APP_URL` for sign-in/get-started CTAs

## Deploy Workflow

1. Change `render.yaml`
2. Commit and push to `main`
3. Render auto-deploys all three services
4. Verify via `/api/health` on the API service
